      </prefercite>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_db91c903d7bc1bf7a8bba78e2f104cd4">
         <head>Content Description</head>
         <p>The collection includes 96 lantern slides on the topic of ophthalmology created by Edward N. DeWitt (1887-1983) for use in lectures and handwritten lecture notes. Topics include tumors, signs of trauma, lectures on anatomy and muscles, and microscopic views of retimas. Slides from lectures I.-IV. are from the Bausch &amp; Lomb "Human eye in anatomical transparencies" series, 1943. Slides in box 1 are black and white, slides in box 2 are in color.</p>
      </scopecontent>
